# Trans Resources

A collection of neat lil &#x1F3F3;&#xFE0F;&#x200D;&#x26A7;&#xFE0F; things that I currently or have read in alphabetical order, along with other resources

## Information

### Blogs
* [Curvy and Trans](https://curvyandtrans.com): A (seemingly dead?) personal blog mostly about trans topics, but also includes other topics such as the general LGBTQ community and mental health
* [Stained Glass Woman](https://stainedglasswoman.substack.com): A weekly publication/newsletter primarily about being trans; includes some science posts, some informative posts, and generally a variety other trans-related posts
* [Tilly's Trans Tuesdays](https://www.tillystranstuesdays.com): A weekly blog chronicling what trans people experience every day, in addition to trans education posts

### Books
* [I'm Afraid of Men](https://www.penguinrandomhouse.ca/campaign/665/im-afraid-men): A short book detailing Vivek Shraya's experiences with toxic masculinity, misogyny, transphobia, and homophobia that has left her scared of men in general

### Reading
* [DIY HRT Directory](https://diyhrt.wiki): A website (not really a wiki) dedicated to documenting how to safely procure, handle, and inject (if applicable) DIY HRT
* [Gender Dysphoria Bible](https://genderdysphoria.fyi): An essay on what gender euphoria and gender dysphoria is, along with the subtypes of dysphoria; includes information about the effects HRT and a collection of trans-related tweets
* [Nonbinary Wiki](https://nonbinary.wiki): A wiki dedicated to non-binary identities and information on transitioning

## Entertainment

### Prose
* [Magical: Before the Magic](https://www.deviantart.com/jocelynsamara/gallery/52095340/before-the-magic): A series of short stories about the lives of four magical and trans school children tasked with saving the school... but before they have attained said magic<br>
  (The story will be primarily told as a webcomic, but there have been four short stories released as prose. For more information about the webcomic, see [the Rainverse Wiki article on _Magical_](https://rainverse.wiki/wiki/Magical))
* [Orange Crushed](https://www.scribblehub.com/series/217918/orange-crushed/): A spin-off short story where a group of students come across a can of orange juice that just-so-happens to change the gender of those who drink it
* [Poor Unfortunate Soul](https://www.scribblehub.com/series/280449/poor-unfortunate-soul/): A short story where we see ourselves as Killian, a genderfluid merperson who recently took up an unusual internship that they spotted while looking for job listings...
* [Teenage Dirtbag](https://www.scribblehub.com/series/298085/teenage-dirtbag/): A novella where the main protagonist, a timid and shy character, is paired up for a biology class project with the hottest girl in the school and her boyfriend
* [The Fox and the Fight](https://www.scribblehub.com/series/377532/the-fox-and-the-fight/): A short story where the main protagonist notices Sawyer Selachi, the swim team ace, bullying someone. He confronts Sawyer, andâ€”thanks to Sawyerâ€”realizes something about herself...
* [The Sable and the Statue](https://www.scribblehub.com/read/460482-santas-secret-transfic-anthology-vol-/chapter/493252/): A story set in the same universe as _The Fox and the Fight_, where we see see ourselves in the eyes of a college dropout who goes back to finish his final project, but unexpected things happen when he tries to start...
* [Trolls and Tribulations](https://www.scribblehub.com/series/161662/trolls-and-tribulations/): A novella where a troll accidentally affirms a closeted trans girl's gender and encourages her to transition, as a prank. Definitely just a prank.
* [What If We Were Both Girls and We Kissed? (In Minecraft)](https://www.scribblehub.com/series/474111/what-if-we-were-both-girls-and-we-kissed-in-minecraft/): ðŸ‘‰ðŸ‘ˆ

### Webcomics
* [I want to be a cute anime girl](https://www.webtoons.com/en/canvas/i-want-to-be-a-cute-anime-girl/list?title_no=349416): A comic about a trans girl, Cheryl, trying to figure out her identity and future as she realizes that she is trans; focuses mostly on trans joy
* [My Impossible Soulmate](https://rainverse.wiki/wiki/My_Impossible_Soulmate): A comic about a demiromantic lesbian, Chiaki Koizumi, trying to live and belong in another world that she fell into, as she tries to find a way to go back into her world so that she can confess her crush to her childhood friend
* [Rain](https://rainverse.wiki/wiki/Rain_(comic)): A comic about a young trans woman, Rain Flaherty, trying to graduate high school while presenting as a girl for her senior year; also just queer in general
* [The Prettiest Platypus](https://www.webtoons.com/en/canvas/the-prettiest-platypus/list?title_no=463063): A comic about a trans girl, Lillie, figuring out herself and her future despite transphobia with the help of her friends and sister

## Other Resources
* [Global Transgender Resources Registry](https://gtrr.artemislena.eu): Links to a variety of resources, including summaries about the law, lists of medical clinics, and local support groups
* [TransHub](https://www.transhub.org.au): A New South Wales, Australia-specific resource on transness in general
* [w/trans/resources](https://raddle.me/wiki/trans/resources): A tiny wiki on Raddle, a small Reddit competitor, that contains links to other trans-related resources
